<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-16"><hi rend="italic">August 16,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The extradition provisions of the Revised Statutes are extended to the
                            Philippine Islands by the act of February 6, 1905, Statutes at Large,
                            volume 33, page 698; it provides that extradition to and from the
                            islands shall be made pursuant to provisions of regular extradition
                            treaties between the United States and other countries.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>